Reasoning: 
1) cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with cut-free nets of linear logic and their strong normalization, which is a topic in mathematical logic. 
2) cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as linear logic has applications in programming language semantics. 
3) cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possibility as linear logic has been used in the development of probabilistic programming languages, which are used in machine learning. 
4) cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as strong normalization is a concept in computational complexity theory. 
5) cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper deals with computing the maximal length of reduction sequences, which is a topic in algorithms.
